RESTToolkit

public RESTToolkit(java.lang.String username,
                   java.lang.String password,
                   java.lang.String controllerURL,
                   java.lang.String params)
AppDynamics Toolkit constructor to initialize user and controller information (EXAMPLE) username: username@customer1 password: xxxx controllerURL: http://localhost:8090 params: &output=JSON If you are using the SaaS Controller, your username is your AppDynamics account name

Parameters:
username - Username of the user making the request
password - Password of the user making the request
controllerURL - URL of the server from where the request is being made (i.e. http://localhost:8090)
params - Further parameters to specify type of return data

Gets the average response time for a business transaction from a specific time range. (INFO) To get current time in milliseconds: System.currentTimeMillis(); To get time from past use SimpleDateFormat (EXAMPLE) SimpleDateFormat format = new SimpleDateFormat("yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss"); format.setTimezone(Timezone.getTimezone("GMT")); Date date = format.parse("2013-01-01 23:59:59"); Time in milliseconds: date.getTime();

Parameters:
app - Application Name or Application ID
BT - Business Transaction Name
startTime - (Milliseconds) Start Time of the Range from which data will be pulled in UNIX epoch time.
endTime - (Milliseconds) End Time of the Range from which the data will be pulled in UNIX epoch time.
rollup - If true, value as single data point is returned. If false, all the values within the specified time range are returned.
Returns:
ArrayList<ADMetric> - List of Metrics
